					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Food and renewable raw materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">A hard candy, or boiled sweet, is a sugar candy prepared from one or more sugar-based syrups that is heated to a temperature of 160 °C to make candy. It is often made from cooking sugar to the point it becomes solid and translucent, with food coloring often added as well as taste. Among the many hard candy varieties are stick candy such as the candy cane, lollipops, rock, aniseed twists, and bêtises de Cambrai.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硬糖，或煮糖，是一种由一个或多个基于糖的糖浆制成的糖果，该糖浆被加热到160°C以制作糖果。它通常是通过烹饪糖到它变得坚硬和透明的程度制成的，通常还会添加食品色素以及口味。在许多硬糖品种中，有棒棒糖如糖果手杖，棒棒糖，岩糖，茴香糖，以及Cambrai的错误。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Sugar-based syrups</sumFormula>
